<div id="wb_element_instance539" class="wb_element" style=" line-height: normal;"><h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ciudad de Buenos Aires | Iguazú | El Calafate | Ushuaia | Crucero Australis</strong></h3>

<h3 class="wb-stl-heading3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>18 DAYS / 16 NIGHTS</strong></h3>

<p> </p>

<p> </p>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>The program includes the following services: </strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>* All destinations: Transfers Airport / Hotel / Airport<br>
* Buenos Aires: 4 night-accommodation in the chosen hotel with breakfast. A Tour along Buenos Aires City. Dinner Tango´s Show.<br>
* Iguazu: 3 night-accommodation in the chosen hotel with breakfast. Excursion to IguazuFalls on Argentinean and Brazilian sides.<br>
* El Calafate: 3 night accommodation in the chosen hotel with breakfast. Excursion to Perito Moreno Glacier bridges.<br>
* Ushuaia: 3 night-accommodation in the chosen hotel with breakfast. Excursion to LagoFagnano off road 4X4 with lunch box<br>
* Autralis Cruise: 3 nigh- accommodation. All Inclusive, and transfer in a private car from Punta Arenas to Rio Gallegos</strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong> </strong></h1>

<p> </p>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Day 1: Europe/America</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>With the south cross as a guide you fly over the Atlantic Ocean to have an unforgettable experience in Argentina with its incredible scenery and wild nature. Enjoy your quiet flight over the ocean to take a rest, and to prepare for what comes next.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 2: Marvellous Buenos Aires</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>The city tour lets you discover the great city located on the Rio de La Plata. Buenos Aires captures her visitors at first sight, specially its numerous cultural options. Highlight: “La Reina del Plata” as it was referred to tango casts a spell on her guest. Theaters, restaurants, cinemas, bars and coffee shops allow you to discover Buenos Aires’s identity.<br>
 </strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Day 3: Free day in Buenos Aires</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Near the city, you can find different lifestyles. On a special country day, you can be indulged with famous “Asado Criollo” and a typical horse show as a part of the “Fiesta Gaucha”. In short, an option you can not miss</strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong> </strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Day 4: Buenos Aires / Iguazu</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>In Iguazu, nature offers you an unforgettable sight. 900 meters of bridges over Rio Iguazu, and the breathtaking Iguazú falls will astonish you.</strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Day 5: Iguazú / “Garganta del Diablo”</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>On the “Jungle Train” you begin a ride to the heart of the Iguazu falls. A walk through the passages allow you to walk among the waterfalls till you reach the “Garganta del Diablo”. The possibility of having a baptism by these spraying waters, on a short boat trip, is an optional excursion that is very difficult to resist.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 6: Brazilian falls</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Enjoy the Iguazú falls from the Brazilian side along 900 meters of bridges.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 7: Iguazú / El Calafate</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>The Glacier air touches your face softly as soon as you get off the plane bringing you from Iguazú. You arrive in “El Calafate” city, the access to the Perito Moreno Glacier.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 8: El Calafate – Perito Moreno Glacier</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>You reach the Glacier walking along the bridges that let you contemplate the magnificent view of the glacier. It is a soundless white river, with blue tones that wait patiently to fall into the “Argentino Lake”.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 9: El Calafate - Free day</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>This region offers numberless options to enjoy The Glaciares National Park.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 10: El Calafate – Ushuaia</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>A very short flight from El Calafate to Ushuaia allows y</strong><strong style="background-color: transparent;">ou to reach the most southern place in the world: Ushuaia, a treat to enjoy throughtout the year.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 11: Ushuaia, Fagnano Lake off road</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>The excursion to Fagnano Lake on a special 4X4 off road trucks, from Ushuaia city traveling across the Southern Andes, to Garibaldi Lake to taste some delicious grilled beef.</strong><br>
 </h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Day 12: Ushuaia, Free day</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>There are several alternatives to enjoy your free day: the amazing excursion to the Tierra del Fuego National Park, or the visit to the uninhabited Gable Island, or –only in winter- a sledge tour pulled by special dogs (huskies).</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 13: Ushuaia / Australis Cruises</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>The Captain and crew give a welcome cocktail reception on board. Immediately afterwards, the ship departs for “the uttermost part of the earth.” This excursion will take us through Beagle Channel and the Strait of Magellan to explore one of the most captivating wilderness regions in the world: Southern Patagonia, and Tierra del Fuego. You have just embarked on a Great Adventure.</strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong> </strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Day 14 – Seno D´Agostini</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>You sail through Beagle and Murray channels to reach and disembark in Cape Horn National Park (weather permitting), on Hornos Island, high rocky promontory. This mythical place is known as the “End of the Earth”; this visit is a singular privilege. The park was declared a World Biosphere Reserve by UNESCO, in June 2005. In the afternoon, we go ashore in the historic Wulaia Bay, once the site of one of the region’s largest aboriginal settlements. This area is also renowned for the mesmerizing beauty of its vegetation and geography. You walk through a Magellan forest of Lengas, Coigües, Canelos, ferns and other native vegetation to reach a lookout point.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 15 – Garibaldi</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>In the afternoon, you view the awe-inspiring Gunther Plüschow Glacier, named after the region’s pioneering German aviator. Then you sail to Chico Sound, where you disembark in Zodiacs to observe the majestic Piloto and Nena glaciers.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 16 - Punta Arenas / Buenos Aires City</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Early in the morning, you go ashore on Magdalena Island, the home of an immense colony of Magellan Penguins that you can watch during our walk to a lighthouse, which guides ships on their way through the Strait of Magellan. In September and April this excursion is replaced by a Zodiac boat ride at Isla Marta to observe sea lions. After our visit, you sail to Punta Arenas, disembarking at 11:30 a.m. Transfer in a private car to Rio Gallegos to take the flight. The plane brings you back to Buenos Aires.</strong><br>
 </h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Day 17: Buenos Aires, Tango Dinner Show</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>You can have a different day taking an excursion to Delta, in Tigre, sailing on a special boat through the channels among the islands, and having lunch near the river. Otherwise you can spend the last day doing your last shopping. Our package includes a Dinner Tango´s Show at Esquina Carlos Gardel, to discover the secrets of the most famous Argentine dance.</strong></h1>

<h2 class="wb-stl-heading2" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Day 18: Buenos Aires, till your next trip</strong></h2>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong>Along your trip you have visited the most stunning region of this planet. Ezeiza International Airport is your last stop before boarding your international flight. End of our services.</strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><br><strong> </strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong> </strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"><strong> </strong></h1>

<h1 class="wb-stl-heading1" style="text-align: center;"> </h1>

